===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /wɜː(r)d/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /w3:(r)d/

===Etymology===

IE ''werə-'', to speak.

===Noun===

#([[w:linguistics|linguistics]]) A distinct unit of language (sounds in speech or written letters) with a particular meaning. Composed of one or more [[morpheme]]s.  It is also composed of [[phoneme]]s that determine its sound pattern.
#Something said or promised.
#([[computer]]s) A numerical value with a [[bit]] width native to the machine
#([[Theological]]) [[God]] @ http://www.ccel.org/bible/kjv/John/1.html

